		"name": "Job Portal API",
		"description": "### üìù **Overview: Job Portal API**\n\nWelcome to the **Job Portal API**, a RESTful API built with Laravel for managing job seekers, companies, job postings, applications, and invitations.\n\nThis API is designed for a job recruitment platform that connects **job seekers** and **companies**, providing features such as:\n\n- User authentication (Login/Register)\n    \n- Managing job seeker and company profiles\n    \n- Creating and browsing job posts\n    \n- Applying to job posts\n    \n- Sending and responding to job invitationsEndFragment\n    \n\n---\n\n### üìö **Main Features**\n\n#### üë§ Authentication\n\n- Register and login with role: `job_seeker` or `company`\n    \n\n#### üßë‚Äçüíº Job Seekers\n\n- CRUD for job seeker profiles\n    \n- Get user basic and full info\n    \n\n#### üè¢ Companies\n\n- CRUD for company information\n    \n- View associated account\n    \n\n#### üìÑ Job Posts\n\n- Companies can create, update, delete job posts\n    \n- Job seekers can view and apply\n    \n\n#### üì• Applications\n\n- Job seekers apply to job posts\n    \n- Companies can accept/reject applications\n    \n\n#### üì¨ Invitations\n\n- Companies invite job seekers\n    \n- Job seekers can accept/reject\n    \n\n---\n\n### üìÇ Collection Structure\n\n- `Auth`: Login and Register\n    \n- `Users`: Job seeker and account info\n    \n- `Companies`: Company details and account\n    \n- `Job Posts`: Job listing management\n    \n- `Applications`: Apply, review, accept/reject\n    \n- `Invitations`: Invite, accept/reject invites\n    \n\n---\n\n### üîß Usage\n\n- Base URL: `{{hostname}}/api`\n    \n- Replace `{{hostname}}` with your local or deployed backend domain\n    \n- Most endpoints use `application/json` as body type",
